Moreover, the market is benefiting from advancements in diagnostic techniques, which are enhancing the accuracy and efficiency of celiac disease diagnosis. As technology continues to evolve, diagnostic tests are becoming more reliable and accessible, allowing healthcare providers to identify celiac disease in patients more effectively. This trend is not only driving growth in the diagnosis segment of the market but also contributing to early detection and timely treatment of the condition, ultimately improving patient outcomes.

Additionally, the treatment segment of the celiac disease market is witnessing substantial growth, primarily driven by the widespread adoption of gluten-free diets as the primary management approach for celiac disease symptoms. The increasing awareness among both healthcare professionals and patients about the importance of adhering to a gluten-free diet is boosting the demand for gluten-free food products and dietary supplements designed specifically for individuals with celiac disease. This shift towards gluten-free living is not only shaping consumer behavior but also creating opportunities for market players to introduce innovative and diverse products that cater to the unique dietary needs of celiac patients.

